    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study of Collection Accounting and 3rd Party Post Paid Billing Process</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Dijil Dev. K. V</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Collection Accounting<br />3rd Party Post Paid Billing Process</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Apr-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5626</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Finance is the life blood and nerve centre of any business and Collection Accounting is the functional areas of finance that covers all the current account of the firm. Understanding as well as proper management of creditors helps in maximizing a company’s potential for its revenue generation.
Collection Accounting involves the relationship between a firm’s Debt and its valuable customers. The goal of Collection Accounting management is to ensure that a firm is able to continue its operations and that it has sufficient ability to satisfy to both maturing short-term debt and upcoming operational expenses. The management of Collection Accounting involves Account Receivable Management(ARM),managing creditors accounts, Managing 3rd Party agencies for the benefit of debt collection, and managing cash. The main sources of collection Accounting are the Consumers, 3rd Party agencies, the short-term assets that the firm can use to generate cash. However, the firm also has investments and so these have to be taken account of when working out how much collection a firm has at its disposal.
If a business is operating profitably, then it should, in theory, generate cash surpluses. If it doesn’t generate surpluses, the business will eventually run out of cash and expire.
The faster a business expands the more cash it will need for working capital and investment. Good management of Collection Process will generate cash and help improve profits and reduce risks.
Sound Collection Process management lie in two fundamental decision issues for the firm. They are the determinant of
 The optimal level of Creditors.
 The appropriate mix of short-term and long term financing used to support the investment.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9766">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9766</a></td></tr>
